1
00:01:35,280 --> 00:01:40,115
You know what they say? The minute they
look at you, bingo, they can read your mind.

2
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:43,033
- You fall for that stuff?
- I'm telling you!

3
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:47,159
So this is where you've
been hiding. Everybody's upstairs.

4
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:50,869
Anyway, so, as I was telling you,
I met this psychic...

5
00:02:00,760 --> 00:02:04,389
Well, if it isn't my favorite
sister and brother act.

6
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:07,235
- Glad you could make it.
- So am I.

7
00:02:07,320 --> 00:02:10,039
You know me. Regular party animal.

8
00:02:12,320 --> 00:02:14,038
So is Dad here yet?

9
00:02:14,120 --> 00:02:17,476
When I left the office
he said he'd be here in 20 minutes.

10
00:02:17,560 --> 00:02:21,838
- That was two hours ago.
- He can spend an entire holiday in the lab.

11
00:02:21,920 --> 00:02:23,273
Yeah.

12
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:26,156
Uh... I guess I'm off to mingle.

13
00:02:30,600 --> 00:02:32,875
Come here, I got something for you.

14
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:39,956
Oh, wait, wait.

15
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:43,190
Merry Christmas.

16
00:02:43,280 --> 00:02:44,633
Alex.

17
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:59,752
It's beautiful.

18
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:03,633
- Put it on.
- Help me.

19
00:03:07,160 --> 00:03:10,357
- I bet you believe in Santa too.
- Give me a break.

20
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:13,910
No, but it's true. This cousin of mine,

21
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:18,630
he knows a guy that was scanned by one
of them at a convention in Des Moines.

22
00:03:18,720 --> 00:03:21,757
- You guys are talking scanners?
- We're talking science fiction.

23
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:24,752
Oh, yeah? Hey, Alex!

24
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:30,759
- What's up, buddy?
- These guys don't believe in scanners.

25
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:32,796
Oh, yeah? Well, they're right.

26
00:03:34,320 --> 00:03:37,835
Don't mind Santa,
he gets a little crazy this time of year.

27
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:40,514
Alex, make believers out of these guys.

28
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:43,512
Come on, give me a break,
it's Christmas Eve.

29
00:03:45,720 --> 00:03:47,472
Party pooper.

30
00:03:50,360 --> 00:03:51,952
Ooh!

31
00:03:52,040 --> 00:03:55,271
That's it. Come on, now,
give me one of those.

32
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:58,636
You know, come on now.
Let's show these guys.

33
00:03:58,720 --> 00:04:01,792
- You're not gonna leave me alone, Taylor.
- Do it.

34
00:04:01,880 --> 00:04:04,678
- You ready?
- Come on, I'm ready.

35
00:04:08,480 --> 00:04:10,550
All right. Hold on to your beard.

36
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:22,480
Whoa.

37
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:26,031
You can do better than that.

38
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:29,152
Whoa!

39
00:04:48,960 --> 00:04:51,155
Man, this guy's incredible.

40
00:04:53,080 --> 00:04:54,991
Come on.

41
00:04:56,360 --> 00:04:58,715
Like I told you, these guys are fantastic.

42
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:01,678
No!

43
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:07,592
No!

44
00:05:07,680 --> 00:05:09,591
Look, Mommy.

45
00:05:11,040 --> 00:05:13,031
Taylor!

46
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:56,471
'Even if I was declared not guilty
for what they called an accident,

47
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:58,516
'I had no choice but to leave.

48
00:05:59,640 --> 00:06:02,154
'I couldn't face my friends, or Joyce.

49
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:06,835
'And I couldn't face the man that adopted
me and my friend Helena,

50
00:06:06,920 --> 00:06:10,629
'taking us out of that horrible
scanners institution.

51
00:06:11,520 --> 00:06:14,512
'I had to find a way to master my powers.

52
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:17,912
'I went around the world

53
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:20,798
'and finally found a place,

54
00:06:20,880 --> 00:06:22,836
'a monastery in Thailand.'

55
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:32,276
I can't believe you talked
a Polish girl into lingerie.

56
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:35,636
- I thought it was just for hookers.
- Come on, Helena.

57
00:06:35,720 --> 00:06:39,872
It's the '90s. We're women, we're strong,
and we can do whatever we want.

58
00:06:39,960 --> 00:06:41,916
Where am I supposed to wear it?

59
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:43,956
Under your clothes.

60
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:47,594
To work, anywhere you feel like it.

61
00:06:47,680 --> 00:06:51,150
Just imagine you and your new boss,
the takeover king.

62
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:56,633
Mark Dragon. Maybe you two could hit it off -
takeover king meets makeover queen.

63
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:58,995
Sounds like a match made in heaven.

64
00:06:59,080 --> 00:07:01,913
Unfortunately, I'm not interested.

65
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:05,310
I know it sounds crazy.
It's been almost two years

66
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:08,597
but even after all this time
I'm still hung up on Alex.

67
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:16,198
Helena, are you all right?

68
00:07:16,280 --> 00:07:20,034
No, not again...
These damn migraines.

69
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:24,272
Any time I get in a crowd
or any pressure situation, I get paralyzed.

70
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:27,352
No wonder I can't hold a job.
How am I supposed to?

71
00:07:27,440 --> 00:07:30,557
Let's get you home.
I know a short cut back to the car.

72
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:35,029
This is what always happens
when I forget my pills.

73
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:37,839
Shouldn't you take them every day?

74
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:42,232
Yes, but they make me stupid like
a sleepwalker. Almost anything is better.

75
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:47,158
Let's get out of here.

76
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:49,993
Well, well, well, what have we got here?

77
00:07:50,080 --> 00:07:53,038
Two uptown babes walking down my street.

78
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:57,193
Whatever you're doing
is none of our business so just let us go.

79
00:07:57,280 --> 00:08:00,352
Didn't you know
it was dangerous in this part of town?

80
00:08:00,440 --> 00:08:03,512
You don't want to do this,
you'll just get into trouble.

81
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:07,752
Thanks for the warning.
But we're not the ones in trouble - you are.

82
00:08:11,120 --> 00:08:13,395
Run, Helena!

83
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:27,358
OK, suck on this.

84
00:08:50,960 --> 00:08:53,235
I think we'd better get out of here.

85
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:12,954
I haven't scanned anyone
since I was 12 years old.

86
00:09:13,040 --> 00:09:15,554
It was pretty amazing.

87
00:09:15,640 --> 00:09:18,234
I just didn't know I had it in me.

88
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:22,871
- I knew Alex could do that, but you?
- Just don't tell Father. Please.

89
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:25,679
Don't worry. Your secret's safe with me.

90
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:34,753
Thanks.

91
00:10:09,640 --> 00:10:11,312
Helena.

92
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:13,958
Helena?

93
00:10:17,360 --> 00:10:19,510
Darling, are you all right?

94
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:21,556
I have a headache, Dad.

95
00:10:21,640 --> 00:10:23,039
Oh.

96
00:10:25,960 --> 00:10:27,916
So you were with Joyce.

97
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:34,112
I just saw her leaving. Hardly recognized her
without her lab coat and clipboard.

98
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:35,349
Here.

99
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:37,476
Take one of these, try to relax.

100
00:10:38,320 --> 00:10:40,675
You know I hate those pills.

101
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:44,638
Well...

102
00:10:45,520 --> 00:10:48,398
I don't want to get your hopes up but...

103
00:10:48,480 --> 00:10:50,789
I have something.

104
00:10:50,880 --> 00:10:54,839
Something which could change your life,
and every other scanner.

105
00:10:59,520 --> 00:11:02,353
That, my darling, is EPH-3,

106
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:04,431
a new delivery system.

107
00:11:04,520 --> 00:11:07,193
Electronically charged skin patches.

108
00:11:07,280 --> 00:11:11,239
You wear it behind the ear and the drug is
absorbed into the bloodstream.

109
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:13,311
One patch should last 24 hours.

110
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:17,188
And you think it'll stop the pain?
And the voices?

111
00:11:17,280 --> 00:11:21,478
I certainly hope so. We've done everything
possible to purify the compound.

112
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:25,431
When can I try it?

113
00:11:25,520 --> 00:11:27,238
As soon as I've finished testing.

114
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:31,279
I hope it's soon cos I can't stand those pills
any longer.

115
00:11:31,360 --> 00:11:34,318
They stop the pain, but everything else too.

116
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:37,631
We don't know,
if any, what the side effects are.

117
00:11:38,360 --> 00:11:41,796
As you know, there's no such thing
as scanner lab rats.

118
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:48,751
Let me work with you on it. I understand
the problem better than anyone.

119
00:11:48,840 --> 00:11:51,229
I can be your personal control group.

120
00:11:51,320 --> 00:11:52,912
Helena.

121
00:11:53,560 --> 00:11:55,676
We've been through this before.

122
00:11:57,160 --> 00:11:59,116
Who are you going to test it on?

123
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:03,318
I've found two terminally ill scanners
who will volunteer.

124
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:05,356
They're at Baumann Clinic.

125
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:09,789
You're working with Dr. Baumann again?

126
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:15,230
That pervert.

127
00:12:15,320 --> 00:12:18,471
It's the only clinic for scanners in the region.

128
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:24,515
I don't want anything to do with EPH-3
if that sadist is going to be involved.

129
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:26,556
Helena, be reasonable.

130
00:12:29,160 --> 00:12:32,277
I'm sorry, Dad, I just have
so much work to do.

131
00:12:32,360 --> 00:12:35,955
- I'm meeting tomorrow with ASN.
- I know. Get some rest.

132
00:12:36,040 --> 00:12:38,474
Go on. You can catch up in the morning.

133
00:12:42,160 --> 00:12:44,549
Stop!

134
00:12:44,640 --> 00:12:46,949
No, stop, please!

135
00:12:47,040 --> 00:12:52,353
The subject demonstrated pain responses
which require further examination.

136
00:12:52,440 --> 00:12:55,671
Quiet, Helena! It doesn't hurt that much!

137
00:13:00,840 --> 00:13:02,876
No, please don't!

138
00:13:06,680 --> 00:13:08,830
Oww! Stop, please.

139
00:13:08,920 --> 00:13:11,514
No, no, no...

140
00:13:12,800 --> 00:13:14,756
No...

141
00:13:23,280 --> 00:13:26,477
'No, stop!'

142
00:15:19,560 --> 00:15:21,391
Eurgh...

143
00:15:25,680 --> 00:15:28,672
Oh, you stupid creature.

144
00:15:44,280 --> 00:15:49,229
- Well, if it isn't my gorgeous goddaughter.
- Well, if it isn't our expensive attorney.

145
00:15:52,160 --> 00:15:56,199
- How do you feel this morning, Helena?
- Like pure electricity.

146
00:15:56,280 --> 00:15:58,236
Well, that's a change.

147
00:15:58,320 --> 00:16:00,311
Yes, it certainly is.

148
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:04,279
So I hear you're taking the world by storm
with Mark Dragon.

149
00:16:04,360 --> 00:16:06,669
- They haven't seen anything yet.
- Oh.

150
00:16:06,760 --> 00:16:09,354
Aren't we the confident one these days?

151
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:11,712
Thanks to Daddy dear.

152
00:16:13,440 --> 00:16:15,237
Have a good day!

153
00:16:26,680 --> 00:16:28,636
What's with her?

154
00:16:30,040 --> 00:16:32,076
I'm not sure. She's been a little...

155
00:16:32,160 --> 00:16:34,674
- flighty lately.
- I see.

156
00:16:36,160 --> 00:16:38,628
So why don't you bring her
into the business?

157
00:16:38,720 --> 00:16:40,756
I'm not convinced she's ready.

158
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:45,034
Oh, you're right.

159
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:49,998
It's Alex. I just feel he should have
something to come home to.

160
00:16:50,760 --> 00:16:54,070
I guess when you adopt children
you always are afraid

161
00:16:54,160 --> 00:16:56,958
that your hold on them is a little tenuous.

162
00:16:58,200 --> 00:17:01,237
Elton... you've adopted them both.

163
00:17:01,320 --> 00:17:03,311
I mean, they're both your children

164
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:07,871
and I think it's time that you faced the fact
that Alex might not be coming back.

165
00:17:08,920 --> 00:17:12,799
So give her a chance.
It could make things easier for both of you.

166
00:17:12,880 --> 00:17:14,836
I've lost Alex, Michael.

167
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:20,196
I don't want to lose her too.

168
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:27,713
ASN Broadcasting.

169
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:32,954
54 TV stations.
Satellite pickup in 15 countries.

170
00:18:34,400 --> 00:18:37,710
Well... here's to
the new kid on the block, Helena.

171
00:18:37,800 --> 00:18:39,836
I'm very flattered, Mr. Dragon.

172
00:18:40,440 --> 00:18:44,797
I didn't know if you realized how much work
I put into the ASN deal.

173
00:18:45,440 --> 00:18:48,273
Not you - me, Mark Dragon.

174
00:18:48,360 --> 00:18:50,555
Takeover king. Your boss.

175
00:18:51,800 --> 00:18:56,590
Oh, come on, Helena. People expect
my employees to do the courting.

176
00:18:56,680 --> 00:18:58,875
And you do it very well.

177
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:02,756
But when it comes to the wedding,
they want me as the groom.

178
00:19:02,840 --> 00:19:05,400
I am always the bridesmaid, never the bride.

179
00:19:05,480 --> 00:19:07,118
It takes time, sweetie.

180
00:19:07,880 --> 00:19:10,678
But if you play your cards right, you'll be fine.

181
00:19:10,760 --> 00:19:13,752
And... what exactly am I doing here,
Mr. Dragon?

182
00:19:14,320 --> 00:19:18,029
You're, um, window dressing.
Know what I mean?

183
00:19:21,720 --> 00:19:23,915
Look who's here.

184
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:27,470
Mr. First World Bank himself.

185
00:19:28,920 --> 00:19:32,879
You wanna be the big cheese one day?
Watch a master at work.

186
00:19:35,880 --> 00:19:39,031
Mr. Crandall. What a surprise.

187
00:19:39,120 --> 00:19:40,792
Ah.

188
00:19:40,880 --> 00:19:42,518
Mark Dragon.

189
00:19:43,120 --> 00:19:46,112
- Mr. Dudswell and Mr. Bentley.
- Won't you join us?

190
00:19:46,200 --> 00:19:49,909
- No, I'd hate to bust up your evening.
- Oh, not at all.

191
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:51,956
- We're just celebrating.
- Oh?

192
00:19:52,040 --> 00:19:56,158
- Are you about to make an announcement?
- Yes. But not the kind you mean.

193
00:19:56,240 --> 00:19:59,391
It's business. A little thing
called ASN Broadcasting.

194
00:19:59,480 --> 00:20:01,835
- I just bought it.
- Oh, really?

195
00:20:01,920 --> 00:20:03,956
How do you plan to finance this?

196
00:20:04,040 --> 00:20:07,271
That's exactly what I wanted
to talk to you about.

197
00:20:08,520 --> 00:20:12,035
Helena Monet, VP finance,
I'm very pleased to meet you.

198
00:20:12,120 --> 00:20:14,839
Always a pleasure to meet a beautiful lady.

199
00:20:15,800 --> 00:20:18,109
Where was I? Erm... Listen, honey,

200
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:20,430
go get us some more champagne, babe.

201
00:20:20,520 --> 00:20:23,876
And one more thing, I...

202
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:26,638
gotta dance!

203
00:20:33,280 --> 00:20:35,111
Look at that guy!

204
00:21:24,600 --> 00:21:27,831
Don't take it personal.
You just fucked with the wrong person.

205
00:21:29,720 --> 00:21:31,199
See ya.

206
00:22:02,920 --> 00:22:05,070
Dr. Baumann.

207
00:22:05,160 --> 00:22:06,718
No one's allowed in here.

208
00:22:06,800 --> 00:22:11,351
Oh, don't worry, Doctor, I'll just take
a moment of your precious time.

209
00:22:11,440 --> 00:22:13,670
Who are you? What do you want?

210
00:22:14,640 --> 00:22:17,598
I guess for you I'm just a distant memory.

211
00:22:17,680 --> 00:22:19,636
But where are your awards?

212
00:22:19,720 --> 00:22:24,077
All those experiments and no recognition
from the psychiatric community.

213
00:22:24,160 --> 00:22:25,718
What a pity.

214
00:22:26,280 --> 00:22:31,115
I thought that your work with that little girl
from Poland was Nobel prize material.

215
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:33,555
What was her name?

216
00:22:33,640 --> 00:22:35,517
Helena Loey.

217
00:22:37,480 --> 00:22:39,072
That's right.

218
00:22:40,320 --> 00:22:41,958
Dear little Helena.

219
00:22:42,040 --> 00:22:44,634
Dear little Helena, my ass!

220
00:22:44,720 --> 00:22:48,793
You were always a brat. And I can see now
that things haven't changed.

221
00:22:48,880 --> 00:22:51,110
You know it's not polite to point.

222
00:22:51,200 --> 00:22:52,713
Where did you get the idea

223
00:22:52,800 --> 00:22:54,870
- that you could waltz in here...
- I said...

224
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:57,713
it's not polite to point.

225
00:23:05,400 --> 00:23:09,518
The subject demonstrated pain responses
which could not be verified

226
00:23:09,600 --> 00:23:11,556
without further examination.

227
00:23:13,520 --> 00:23:17,069
- Still a photographer, though, I see.
- I...

228
00:23:17,160 --> 00:23:20,630
I was just trying to help you.
There was no other way.

229
00:23:20,720 --> 00:23:25,271
I guess I should have felt honored
being your favorite lab rat, but I didn't.

230
00:23:25,360 --> 00:23:27,590
I felt like shit!

231
00:23:58,760 --> 00:24:00,478
Now what do you say?

232
00:24:02,640 --> 00:24:03,993
I'm sorry!

233
00:24:04,080 --> 00:24:06,230
No, that's not it.

234
00:24:06,960 --> 00:24:10,077
Look at the camera, Doctor. Come on.

235
00:24:29,920 --> 00:24:33,515
Darn, I hate the way the flash
makes their eyes go red.

236
00:24:46,240 --> 00:24:48,196
Hey, lady. Looking for someone?

237
00:24:53,480 --> 00:24:55,835
Work, work, work.

238
00:25:06,160 --> 00:25:08,196
You're starting to piss me off.

239
00:25:12,320 --> 00:25:14,356
Oh, shit.

240
00:25:14,440 --> 00:25:17,238
That too can be arranged.

241
00:25:19,080 --> 00:25:20,638
Gotta get out of here.

242
00:25:22,440 --> 00:25:26,069
Oh, I hope you're not going to shoot me
with that.

243
00:25:28,680 --> 00:25:30,989
That's better. Now come here.

244
00:25:31,760 --> 00:25:33,193
Yeah, that's it.

245
00:25:33,280 --> 00:25:37,114
Just a little closer so we can
get to know each other better.

246
00:25:39,840 --> 00:25:42,638
Did you ever play doctor
when you were a kid?

247
00:25:42,720 --> 00:25:44,711
Uh-huh.

248
00:25:44,800 --> 00:25:46,870
It was fun, wasn't it?

249
00:25:46,960 --> 00:25:48,996
Do you want to play it now?

250
00:25:49,080 --> 00:25:50,433
OK.

251
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:54,356
